entries.title: Twitter account that tracked Elon Musk’s jet is suspended permanently
entries.description: Musk, a self-described “free speech absolutist,” had been critical of the account but pledged last month to keep it online.

entries.title: FTX crypto implosion focuses scrutiny on SEC chief Gensler
entries.description: After the FTX implosion and arrest of its founder, some lawmakers are pushing for more action from the SEC.

entries.title: ‘God of War Ragnarok’ director talks about managing team burnout
entries.description: "God of War" director Eric Williams talks about the game's Game Awards wins, Chris Judge's speech, and whether video games should be more like movies.

entries.title: Tech industry group sues to block California children’s safety law
entries.description: The lawsuit is the latest salvo in a battle over the future of the role of states in regulating Silicon Valley.

entries.title: They came to TikTok for fun. They got stuck with sexualized videos
entries.description: Social media algorithms use sex and shock to hook new users. Escaping and understanding what the apps are really tracking takes time.

entries.title: Tom Brady pushed crypto to his fans. This lawyer wants him to pay up.
entries.description: South Florida attorney Adam Moskowitz wants celebrity endorsers to pay for assuring investors that FTX was a safe place for their money.

entries.title: QAnon is finding new life in Elon Musk’s conspiracy theories
entries.description: Musk has become so popular in QAnon circles that some regard him, not Trump, as the savior-like figure they’ve been waiting for.
